&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you self-motivated, enthusiastic and looking for a challenge?  Would you like the opportunity to join our friendly, supportive and dynamic team?  &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dynamic Health, part of Cambridgeshire Community Services, is the leading Musculoskeletal (MSK) and Physiotherapy provider across Cambridgeshire and Peterborough.  We are looking for an administrator with a positive approach, excellent interpersonal and communication skills.  &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a fantastic opportunity to join our team within our Cambridge locality for 18.75 hours per week.  You will work as an Administrator based at Brookfield’s campus, working with and assisting the wider clinical team, delivering Physiotherapy and Specialist Services to Cambridgeshire and Peterborough.  We are committed to high quality and evidence-based care in everything we do. We have a strong track record of service redesign to bring patients out of hospitals into the community setting. We drive innovation and new ways of working, putting Service Users at the centre of our care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for someone who is a team player who will share our values and strive to help us continue on our journey to providing the best of patient care and experience.  Full support and training will be provided for the right candidate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;  For an informal discussion about this post or to arrange a visit to see us&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; Please contact Ellie McNally: &lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Eleanor.McNally@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Interviews will take place via Remote (Digital) Interview via Microsoft Teams&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
